 {"id":"br-r37-c1-qyx9u","title":"parity: top-level isomorphism module missing","description":"NetworkX exposes nx.isomorphism as a top-level module containing GraphMatcher, DiGraphMatcher, ISMAGS, time-respecting matchers, match helper constructors, is_isomorphic, vf2pp_* helpers, and tree isomorphism helpers. FrankenNetworkX currently exports these names only at top level and lacks fnx.isomorphism / import franken_networkx.isomorphism. Add a module object backed by the FrankenNetworkX wrappers and register it in sys.modules, plus parity tests proving the module points at the wrapper classes/functions.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:37:49.312623478Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:42:21.985411035Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:42:21.983510716Z","close_reason":"Completed in 56128df","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-rnxtc","title":"parity: dag colliders/has_cycle/v_structures + structuralholes mutual_weight wrappers (5 functions)","description":"Five missing nx wrappers across two domains. DAG (causal graph helpers): colliders(G), has_cycle(G), v_structures(G). Structural holes (Burt 1992 weight helpers): mutual_weight(G, u, v, weight=None), normalized_mutual_weight(G, u, v, norm=sum, weight=None). Add Python wrappers in __init__.py via _call_networkx_for_parity (top-level nx exports both directly), export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:27:40.051603203Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:44:40.729217982Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T20:44:40.727284532Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 674c3fc: 5 wrappers (has_cycle/colliders/v_structures/mutual_weight/normalized_mutual_weight) all verified against nx on DAG, Bayesian-net DAG, and weighted bidirectional DiGraph.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-sgjko","title":"parity: time-respecting isomorphism matchers missing","description":"NetworkX exposes TimeRespectingGraphMatcher(G1, G2, temporal_attribute_name, delta) and TimeRespectingDiGraphMatcher(G1, G2, temporal_attribute_name, delta). FrankenNetworkX does not export these classes, leaving temporal VF2 matcher API unavailable. Add wrappers that convert FrankenNetworkX graph objects via _networkx_graph_for_parity and delegate to NetworkX, plus parity tests for signatures and isomorphism mappings on temporal graph/digraph paths.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:31:58.717555427Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:35:34.565138940Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:35:34.563236879Z","close_reason":"Completed in 739ccaa","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-uuo38","title":"parity: classes.filters hide_*/show_*/no_filter wrappers (11 fns)","description":"networkx.classes.filters exposes 11 filter factory functions used to construct subgraph views: hide_nodes(nodes), hide_edges(edges), hide_diedges(edges), hide_multiedges(edges), hide_multidiedges(edges), show_nodes(nodes), show_edges(edges), show_diedges(edges), show_multiedges(edges), show_multidiedges(edges), no_filter(*items). franken_networkx does not surface these. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level + __all__. Each returns a filter callable used by subgraph_view.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T22:49:38.907487801Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T22:54:42.507042701Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-vw7p2","title":"parity: connectivity is_locally_k_edge_connected missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.connectivity.is_locally_k_edge_connected(G, s, t, k) tests local k-edge-connectivity between s and t. Not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrapper delegating to networkx and export at top-level.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:51:45.929293966Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T13:04:46.859016482Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T13:04:46.857171079Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 4eb0d6d: is_locally_k_edge_connected verified P5/K4","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"br-r37-c1-wjv9o","title":"parity: tree.branchings + tree.mst edge iterators (5 fns)","description":"Five tree-related utilities from networkx.algorithms.tree not surfaced. Branchings: branching_weight(G, attr=weight, default=1), minimal_branching(G, *, attr=weight, default=1, preserve_attrs=False, partition=None). MST edge iterators: boruvka_mst_edges, kruskal_mst_edges, prim_mst_edges (all signature G, minimum, weight=weight, keys=True, data=True, ignore_nan=False, partition optional). These give users access to the underlying MST/branching algorithm primitives. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level + __all__.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T22:24:47.743148985Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T22:29:40.541414102Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-wjv9o","title":"parity: tree.branchings + tree.mst edge iterators (5 fns)","description":"Five tree-related utilities from networkx.algorithms.tree not surfaced. Branchings: branching_weight(G, attr=weight, default=1), minimal_branching(G, *, attr=weight, default=1, preserve_attrs=False, partition=None). MST edge iterators: boruvka_mst_edges, kruskal_mst_edges, prim_mst_edges (all signature G, minimum, weight=weight, keys=True, data=True, ignore_nan=False, partition optional). These give users access to the underlying MST/branching algorithm primitives. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level + __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T22:24:47.743148985Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T22:39:41.161615863Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T22:39:41.159730985Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 7cca063: branching_weight + minimal_branching + boruvka/kruskal/prim mst_edges iterators. All 5 verified on weighted K5 (MSTs match nx exactly) and 3-node DiGraph (branching weight + edge count match).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-wpydo","title":"parity: community leiden_communities + leiden_partitions missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.community.leiden_communities(G, ...) and leiden_partitions(G, ...) (Leiden community detection algorithm) not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrappers delegating to nx.algorithms.community via _call_networkx_community_for_parity. Export both at top-level and include in __all__ under community detection section.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T12:06:41.073069778Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T13:05:29.824008425Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T13:05:29.822140820Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 4eb0d6d: leiden_communities/partitions wrappers; mirrors nx NotImplementedError parity","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-wxjtp","title":"parity: utils.rcm + utils.misc test-helpers wrappers (7 functions)","description":"Two clusters of nx utilities not surfaced by franken_networkx. (1) RCM ordering family from networkx.utils.rcm: cuthill_mckee_ordering(G, heuristic), connected_cuthill_mckee_ordering(G, heuristic), pseudo_peripheral_node(G) — companions to the already-shipped reverse_cuthill_mckee_ordering. (2) Test/utility helpers from networkx.utils.misc: edges_equal(edges1, edges2, *, directed=False), graphs_equal(g1, g2), nodes_equal(nodes1, nodes2), make_list_of_ints(sequence) — heavily used by nx test suites. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level and adding to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T21:38:45.270718699Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T21:53:49.014765622Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T21:53:49.012666712Z","close_reason":"Shipped in d7024ad: RCM ordering family (cuthill_mckee_ordering, connected_cuthill_mckee_ordering, pseudo_peripheral_node) + test helpers (edges_equal, graphs_equal, nodes_equal, make_list_of_ints). All 7 verified on P8/numpy/tuple cases.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-xditv","title":"parity: fruchterman_reingold_layout numeric parity with networkx","description":"fnx.fruchterman_reingold_layout / spring_layout share signatures with nx but numeric outputs are not pinned to nx for the same seed and graph. Add a parity test (tests/python/test_layout_parity.py) that builds a small fixed graph (path_graph(6), complete_graph(5), karate_club_graph), seeds with seed=42, and compares fnx vs nx node positions within tolerance 1e-6. If divergence, route to nx via _call_networkx_for_parity when method='auto' to preserve drop-in behavior.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T06:14:51.495203398Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T06:18:38.622702670Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T06:18:38.620786474Z","close_reason":"Completed in 82fb1eb","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
